<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><div style="font-family: arial;"><div style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial;">Hi {!Contact.FirstName},<br></font><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>Thank you for getting in touch with Kingsbridge.&nbsp;<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>We’re sorry to hear you do not wish to renew your policy with us this year. To honour your cancellation request, please rest assured that&nbsp;<u>your policy has now been removed from our renewal process</u>.&nbsp;<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>We understand that there can be many reasons why you may not want to continue keeping your business covered with Kingsbridge. However, we want to make sure you’re fully aware of the financial risks that can present from not holding current business insurance if any apply to you.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br><b>Not currently working?</b><br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>If you are not currently working, we would discourage you from cancelling your policy; unless you’re stopping self-employment altogether, a break in cover could affect your business. Our automatic renewal process is in place to ensure you are continuously protected.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br><i>(Use if holding PI)&nbsp;</i>Your package of insurance includes Professional Indemnity cover. This element of the policy works on a ‘claims made’ basis, meaning&nbsp;<u>you must have cover in place at the time of the claim and not at the time of the incident for your policy to provide cover</u>.&nbsp;<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br><i>(Use if holding PI)</i>&nbsp;<b><u>If you choose to cancel your Kingsbridge insurance policy and do not hold alternative cover elsewhere your business will not be covered</u></b>&nbsp;against claims of negligence.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>Any claims for the&nbsp;<i>(delete as appropriate)</i>&nbsp;Public Liability, Employers’ Liability, Contract Works, Own Plant and Hired in Plant elements for the time your policy was active <i>(DD MMM YYYY to DD MMM YYYY)</i> can be notified to insurers. Please refer to your policy wording&nbsp; for full information.&nbsp;<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>If you’ve changed your mind about cancelling your cover after having read the above information and would instead like your policy to renew, please reply to this email and our customer service team will be happy to help.&nbsp;<br></span><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial;"><br>Kind regards,<br></font><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial;"><br>{!User.FirstName}<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial;">Customer Service Team<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial;"><br>E:&nbsp;</span><a href="mailto:customersupport@kingsbridge.co.uk" style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial;">customersupport@kingsbridge.co.uk</a><br><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial;">T: 01242 808 740</span></div></div></div>]]></td>
</tr>
</table>